Description . Measurements. Males: 3.8–5.2 mm ( holotype 4.0 mm), females: 4.3–5.3 mm . Dorsal side oval (
Fig. 85
), convex, glabrous, with very sparse short setae on apical and lateral elytral slopes. Body, legs and antennae metallic bluish-black, mouthparts black, abdomen yellow.

Prosternal proces elevated and thinly visible between procoxae. Posterior margin of last ventrite with shallow indistinct incisions (
Fig. 104
).

Female. Last ventrite transverse with posterior margin widely rounded (
Fig. 106
). Pygidium subtriangular with widely rounded apex (
Fig. 105
). Sternite VIII small, pentagonal, tignum slender, three times longer than sternite VIII (
Fig. 103
). Spermatheca: nodulus wider, gradually continuing to cornu, cornu C-shaped, proximal spermathecal duct gradually narrowing to base (
Fig. 102
).
